#compdef fuzzuli
# =============================================================================
# fuzzuli — musana's "url fuzzing tool that aims to find critical
#            backup files by creating a dynamic wordlist based on
#            the domain."  A specialized security-research tool
#            that:
#              - Takes a list of target domains (from stdin or
#                `-f file`)
#              - For each domain, GENERATES a DYNAMIC WORDLIST of
#                candidate backup filenames derived from the
#                domain name itself (e.g., for `example.com` it
#                tries example.bak, example.zip, examp1e.tar.gz,
#                etc., applying mutation methods like:
#                  - regular (verbatim domain name)
#                  - withoutdots (replace dots with empty)
#                  - withoutvowels (drop vowels)
#                  - reverse (reverse the domain string)
#                  - mixed (random case mutations)
#                  - withoutdv (drop both dots and vowels)
#                  - shuffle (random char shuffle))
#              - Combines each mutated name with backup-file
#                extensions: .rar, .zip, .tar.gz, .tar, .gz, .jar,
#                .7z, .bz2, .sql, .backup, .war, .bak, .dll
#              - Sends HEAD requests to each candidate URL with
#                configurable concurrency (default 16 workers)
#              - Reports URLs that return matching status codes +
#                content types + minimum content lengths
#            Designed for bug-bounty hunters + penetration testers
#            looking for accidentally-deployed source-code backups,
#            database dumps, or sensitive archives left on
#            production web servers.  Maintained by musana
#            (Turkish security researcher) since 2022.
#
# Author:  musana (Ferit Yalçınkaya) — Turkish bug-bounty hunter +
#          web security researcher.  Created fuzzuli in 2022 as
#          tooling for his personal bug-bounty research; gained
#          popularity in 2023-2024 within the Turkish bug-bounty
#          community and beyond.
# Source:  https://github.com/musana/fuzzuli
# CLI:     fuzzuli.go (uses projectdiscovery/goflags for argv
#                       parsing + schollz/progressbar/v3 for
#                       progress display + gammazero/workerpool
#                       for concurrent request workers +
#                       hashicorp/go-retryablehttp for HTTP retry
#                       logic)
# Library: projectdiscovery/goflags
#          ("A go flag wrapper with convenience helpers" — Project
#           Discovery's Go argv-parsing library used across their
#           entire security-tools suite: nuclei, httpx, subfinder,
#           naabu, katana, dnsx, tlsx, interactsh, etc.  Goflags
#           extends Go's stdlib `flag` package with FLAG GROUPS,
#           short+long flag aliases, environment-variable backing,
#           and config-file integration.)
# License: MIT
# Status:  Active — 942+ stars on musana/fuzzuli (last pushed
#          2023-08); goflags itself is 92+ stars on projectdiscovery/
#          goflags (continuous development since 2020 by Project
#          Discovery team — its low star count reflects internal-
#          tooling provenance; despite low GitHub stars, goflags
#          powers a security-tools ecosystem with 100k+ aggregate
#          stars across nuclei + httpx + subfinder + naabu).
#
